<br>
You have been playing over 2 years but I have never heard of you.  And you used a very recent example of a guild in your argument.  Implies lack of experience, when Jeet's argument used guilds and was speaking of a time well beyond Ascent.  It is like comparing apples to oranges.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Actually I think the list has gotten silly, but I also think the way EiE has chosen to deal with it is wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
They did not do anything wrong, except reply to a request for help from an ally that I can see.  Since when is that wrong?<br>
<br>
&quot;I've said from the beginning that no Verant rules were broken. But yes, I'm arguing for what's &quot;right&quot; or &quot;fair&quot; if you want to put it that way. Rules/laws seldom cover everything and people still have a lot of choice about whether to treat each other with respect or to not do so without violating any rules/laws. &quot;<br>
<br>
From everything I have read, Melissa tried to make contact with the clerics on the hill.  When that failed she moved on the spawn.  She made an effort.  I guess she did not work hard enough for some though.  I can think of a lot of people who would not of waited as long as she did.  On the Cleric board it states she was in zone for close to an hour, that is a long time for the AFK's to respond.  An hour seems like a healthy amount of respect to me.<br>
<br>
&quot;  Actually I don't know the cleric who was camping it at all&quot;<br>
<br>
Then why are you so involved?  I know the cleric being flamed and I also in her guild.  <br>
<br>
