No one is going to respect or look up to the power of someone who takes all they can get and runs....especially if the little guy is hurt in the process.  Well ok... maybe SOME people will look up to it, but imo, those people are often just as twisted in their thinking, and no better than the first person.  <br>
Personally I have a number of friends in top tier guilds that I believe to be VERY honorable and decent...  they have my respect, and I believe have earned their power.  But there are always those in powerful positions who abuse it.  These are the people who do their guild tag a disservice and give it a bad name.  <br>
As for Melissa, she did not give DA a bad name in my eyes, but I do still believe she acted in an underhanded, sneaky manner.  No, I do NOT think she did the right thing... and she did not make enough effort to contact people.  It really seems to me that she put out the absolute minimal effort she thought she could get away with, and then hid behind the &quot;rules&quot; as her defense.  Sure....maybe that protects her from the rules and those who follow them strictly, but not those of us who consider ourselves to be honorable and put ourselves in her shoes.  I know I would never have done what she did, therefore I can not respect it.  <br>
<br>
~Jazzmine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/udainann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dainann</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(7/24/02 6:41:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/ildanoch/animwolfr.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some clarification to the now locked RF thread</span><hr size=1> The only think relative to the ragefire comments about uber guilds is that the have the experience to mobilize quickly. I could be jealous of their gear and their smooth working teams but face it.. they play a LOT more than the most of us. They work hard for it. Just as in RL a part time employee wont have the experience or get the pay of a full time employee.<br>
